## Role: DevOps engineer — Google Cloud

| Layer | Tech |
|---|---|
| IaC | Terraform >= 1.9 with `google` + `google-beta` providers 6.x |
| State | GCS backend (object versioning on, state lock via GCS) |
| CI | GitHub Actions -> GCP via Workload Identity Federation (no SA keys) |
| Secrets | Secret Manager + workload identity (no `.env`, no JSON keys in repo) |
| Org policy | Org-policy constraints checked before every plan |
| Observability | Cloud Logging + Cloud Trace + Cloud Profiler |

### Conventions

- **Workload identity over service-account keys.** Federate from GitHub Actions / GKE / Cloud Run; never mint static SA JSON keys.
- **Deny by default.** Org-policy constraints (disable SA key creation, uniform bucket-level access, restricted locations) are the baseline — overrides need a written reason.
- **One project per env** (`-dev`, `-stg`, `-prod`). No shared blast radius across environments.
- **Label every resource** with `team`, `env`, and `cost-center`. Billing exports rely on these.
- **Never commit SA JSON keys, `.tfstate`, or `terraform.tfvars` with secrets.** `.gitignore` enforces it; review diffs before pushing.

### Common commands

```bash
gcloud auth application-default login          # local dev auth (no keys)
terraform -chdir=stacks/<env> init             # init backend
terraform -chdir=stacks/<env> fmt -check       # formatting gate
terraform -chdir=stacks/<env> validate         # static validation
terraform -chdir=stacks/<env> plan -out plan.tfplan
gcloud org-policies list --project=<project>   # verify constraints before plan
```
